Basic Sphinx Setup
------------------

https://docs.readthedocs.io/en/latest/getting_started.html

::

  pip install -U sphinx sphinx-autobuild
  cd docs
  sphinx-quickstart 
  ll
  vi index.rst 
  make html



Make Project README part of Sphinx Docs
---------------------------------------

my ``getting_started`` page sources the project readme::

  > cat index.html
  Welcome to Organizer's documentation!
  =====================================
  
  .. toctree::
     :maxdepth: 2
     :caption: Contents:
  
     getting_started


  > cat getting_started.rst 
  :tocdepth: 2
  
  .. include:: ../README.rst


Sphinx AutoDoc Setup
--------------------

The strategy is to run ``sphinx-apidoc`` command as a preprocessor to
``sphinx-build``.  This traverses my package modules and generates
ReSTructuredText from class, function, and method definitions and their
associated docstrings.  These are written into the sphinx source directory and
tied into the ``index.html`` toctree::

  > cat index.html
  Welcome to Organizer's documentation!
  =====================================
  
  .. toctree::
     :maxdepth: 2
     :caption: Contents:
  
     getting_started
     _api/modules


During sphinx-quickstart I accepted extentions for ``autodoc`` and ``napolean``::

  > grep -A4 ^extensions conf.py 
  extensions = [
      'sphinx.ext.autodoc',
      'sphinx.ext.napoleon',
  ]

Then I added an extra ``apidoc`` target and params to the ``Makefile``::

> git diff Makefile
  diff --git a/docs/Makefile b/docs/Makefile
  --- a/docs/Makefile
  +++ b/docs/Makefile

   SOURCEDIR     = .
   BUILDDIR      = _build
  +APIDOCBUILD      = sphinx-apidoc
  +APIDOCHEADER     = 'Organizer API'
  +APIDOCBUILDDIR   = $(SOURCEDIR)/_api
  +APIDOCSOURCEDIR  = ../organizer
   
  +apidoc:
  +       @rm -r $(APIDOCBUILDDIR)
  +       @$(APIDOCBUILD) -H $(APIDOCHEADER) -M -e -o $(APIDOCBUILDDIR) $(APIDOCSOURCEDIR)
  +

  -%: Makefile
  -       @$(SPHINXBUILD) -M $@ "$(SOURCEDIR)" "$(BUILDDIR)" $(SPHINXOPTS) $(O)
  +%: apidoc Makefile
  +       @$(SPHINXBUILD) -M $@ "$(SOURCEDIR)" "$(BUILDDIR)" $(SPHINXOPTS) $(O)



